{{Infobox document |document_name=Karyes Typikon |image=Karyes Typicon and Sava's signature.jpg |image_width=200px |image_caption=The original document with the authentic signature of Sava |date_created=1199 |date_ratified= |location_of_document=[[Mount Athos]] |writer=[[Saint Sava|Monk Sava]] |signers= |purpose=[[Typikon]] }}
The '''Karyes Typikon''' ({{lang-sr|Карејски типик/Karejski tipik}}) was written for the [[Karyes, Mount Athos|Karyes]] cell on [[Mount Athos]] in 1199 by [[Saint Sava]], at the time a [[monk]] and later the first [[Serbs|Serbian]] [[Archbishop]]. It is basically a translation from a standard Greek ascetic typikon with some minor changes. It became a model for Serbian solitary or eremitical monasticism also outside of Mount Athos.<ref name=Bogdanovic-Karejski>{{harvnb|Bogdanović|1999|loc= Предговор, para. 13, Карејски типик}}</ref> It is published along with the Catalog of Cyrillic manuscripts from the [[Hilandar monastery]] since 1908.
